                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Let me start by saying that I love Mr D.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_cool.gif" alt="icon_cool.gif" border="0" /> Level 1 is definately one of our coolest and most useful aa's, and I've used it constantly since I picked up Mr D last week.
<br />

<br />
So yeah, level 1 is pretty cool ... but until I have about 1000 aa points, there's no way I'm picking up levels 2 or 3.
<br />

<br />
I mean, come on! A few more hit points? pffffffffffft How unoriginal for what is actually a pretty original little ability.
<br />

<br />
So I'm starting a new crusade ... I want to get Mr D upgraded and make him worth of the 10 and 15 points it'd cost to upgrade to levels 2 and 3.
<br />

<br />
As I see it, there's one main problem with Doppleganger right now - it only grabs aggro off one mob. I tested out in Freeport by pulling three green guards so they were all hitting me. I cast Doppleganger, got ported away ... and only 1 guard was occupied - the other two continued after me. I'd like to see this changed.
<br />

<br />
So these are the two things I'd like to see added to the Doppleganger ability. Nothing extravagent, and I'm sure nothing anybody who'se used Mr D hasn't thought themselves.
<br />

<br />
Level 2 - Reduce timer to 15 minutes
<br />
Level 3 - Fading Memories type effect.
<br />

<br />
That's it. Make Mr D usable more often, and at level 3 (after spending 34 aa points), give us Fading Memories.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />It's easy to use - if you're one of the 2% of the population who thinks logically and can read an instruction manual. The other 98% of the population would find it very hard or impossible to use.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
