                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Based on the <a href="http://dictionary.reference.com/search?r=2&q=doppelganger" target="_blank" class="postlink">dictionary definition of doppleganger</a>, I think we got off pretty damn lucky.
<br />

<br />
I mean, it could be something like this:
<br />

<br />
Level 1:  Summons an exact copy of you that fights along with your current opponents using melee weapons.
<br />

<br />
Level 2:  Summons an exact copy of you that fights along with your current opponents using nukes and mezzes on your support classes.
<br />

<br />
Level 3:  Summons an exact copy of you that fights along with your current opponents using nukes and mezzes on your support classes.  Killing this dopple results in a major faction hit to all factions in the game except for Janitors of the Plane of Justice and Toilet-Lickers of Rivervale.
<br />

<br />
This would be a real doppleganger in that it would truly haunt it's fleshy counterpart.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=811231" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.blaynesucks.com/images/Bellanfear.gif" border="0" /></a>
<br />
