                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">And at the very least, if they cannot find a way to make tier 2 and 3 useful for it, they could always give us a refund &gt;&lt;
<br />

<br />
Could it be coded to act as a PC as far as aggro?  When it pops, have enchanter's aggro transfered to DG +1 so that it holds the aggro as a "reliable" off-tank until someone else pis...ticks it off more.  Throw some real hp on it (2k, 5k, 10k?) and make it unable to be healed.  That way you haven't ditched aggro on someone that's already built it up.  At this point, you'd have to have people stop hitting the mob (DG would build no aggro after being used, ie; single warrior taunt and then just melee).  10k in GoD would buy you at least a little bit of time to figure out something, be it mez or whatnot without another PC taking the rap for it.
<br />

<br />
