                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">First, a question for clarification.  My view of hate and agro is the following:  A creature's hate list is a list of things that it hates ordered by how much it hates them.  A person can be said to have agro if they are on the hate list, but agro is sometimes also used to refer to the person on the TOP of the hate list.  Agro is also used as a measurement of hate in a similar way as mileage is used to measure distance.  Is this correct?
<br />

<br />
Second, my understanding of pet agro is that if your pet is beating on something, <span style="font-weight: bold">you will share agro to the extent that you are added to the hate list.</span>  If you charm something that is on the hate list for another creature, you are added to the hate list as well (this is what causes the mobs to run after one another).  If it was as simple as just the mob that was charmed being on the hate list in the case that I described, then the pet should have been killed by the mobs when you exodus'd.   Thus, it would be dead and not simply have wandered back to where ever it was waiting for you to recharm it.
<br />

<br />
However, if your pet is beating on something, you do not get any more agro from each additional attack.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=811231" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.blaynesucks.com/images/Bellanfear.gif" border="0" /></a>
<br />
