                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> If it was as simple as just the mob that was charmed being on the hate list in the case that I described, then the pet should have been killed by the mobs when you exodus'd.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Well, not necessarily. Mobs on the same faction will NOT attack one another, so even if they are on each others hate lists, they'll just ignore one another.
<br />

<br />
But yes. To sum up:
<br />

<br />
Sending your pet to attack something gives you hate.  This is true for charmed and summoned pets alike. (Ask any mage about /pet attack aggro)
<br />

<br />
Damage your pet does does NOT give you any hate.
<br />

<br />
Also, these rules are probably different for controlled pets vs 'swarm' pets. (I.e. I strongly suspect that 'swarm' pets add less hate when sent in to attack than 'real' pets.)</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
