                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Unmei wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Don't we get 50% of the aggro our pets generate, or is that strictly from charmed pets?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
We had a discussion about this elsewhere, but the general consensus is:
<br />

<br />
Pets add VERY little hate. Even charmed ones.
<br />

<br />
I'm pretty sure that they THOUGHT about making charmed pets share hate with their owners, but decided against it.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Actually, pets add quite abit of hate.  It has been tamed down abit, but it still transfers a portion, even if you pass the 4 target limit to negate the pet's personal agro, you still get your share.
<br />

<br />
This is mostly noticable when you try to sit, but can also be seen when you have a pet with insane dps.  Also, seems to matter if you have any active agro on your own.  If I haste/dual wield a heavy hitting pet in the mountain trials, for example, it can be hard to find a tank who can keep agro (off of me) if I'm also casting on the mobs (tash and slow).
<br />

<br />
If I don't cast on them, then the mob doesn't seem to care, all the agro is still "passive", even if significant.
<br />

<br />

<br />
But, just the fact that if I sit and send a pet to attack a mob, the mob will come right for me shows that I do get agro transfered, the only question to really debate is how much, not if.  Indirect agro is similiar to assist agro from mobs.  4 mobs might assist the one my pet goes after, but if I sit, they all come for me. (if my pet has damaged the one he's engaging enough, then that one will stay with the pet)  When I stand back up (before they get to me), they'll go after whoever is closest, me or the pet (treats us has having equal agro).
<br />

<br />
Now, if my pet does engage a mob, and builds up enough agro to keep the mobs attention, thats all fine and good... but then say 3 people from my group decide to engage the mob, (or get agro in one form or another), then that puts the hate list over 4 targets (me, pet, and 3 group members = 5) and the pet agro is negated.  That mob will make a beeline right for me, and a tank will have a hard time getting it off me.  On the plus side, a successful taunt will surpase the pets agro (even if "negated", I believe) and thus someone with taunt can keep agro as long as they get enough successful taunts during the course of the fight to keep their agro higher than mine.  
<br />

<br />
Try using a monk to tank for a charmed pet and you'll see what I mean.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=378985" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Tashim</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.botsguild.org/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Brotherhood of the Spider</a>, <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Rathe</a>
<br />

