                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well, in 3boxing a cleric, enc and warrior for mountain trials, I have absolutely no problems with agro when I have just the 4 targets (3 toons + 1 pet).  This allows the pet to build up a ton of agro, but the mob will still fight players that are in range, effectively letting the pet taunt for the tank (as long as I stay out of melee range).
<br />

<br />
However, adding anyone else to the mix negates the pet agro, and I hafta work significantly harder to keep agro, even moreso when the pet is hasted & dual wielding.  
<br />

<br />
It is an ongoing fight to maintain agro; If I just get agro with the tank and then leave him on auto-attack without continuing to taunt, then the agro transfered from the pet will soon overtake the warrior's pathetic dps (compared to the charmed pet) and I'll end up with a dead chanter.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=378985" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Tashim</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.botsguild.org/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Brotherhood of the Spider</a>, <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Rathe</a>
<br />

