                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Nice hijack! 
<br />

<br />
My experience is that pet DPS adds significant aggro.  Consider..
<br />

<br />
With pet tanking in a hard ldon, on pet breaks the wizard gets the target mob's aggro.  (Even if he only nuked once) In Mountain trials on pet breaks, I ALWAYS get aggro.  The only real difference in these scenarios is pet dps as I rarely haste a hard ldon pet.
<br />

<br />
I also group with 2 different mages (seperately) on occasion, one has a much better pet than the other.  When pulling, if I land a mez late... it will beeline for the mage with the better pet.  When I group with the other mage, the mob either stays on me or jumps a melee.
<br />

<br />
Hardly conclusive, but enough to convince me.  Basically, the more dps on a pet, the more aggro the PET has... and thus the more aggro is transfered to you as well.  If pet aggro transference were fixed, mages could nuke the same amount no matter which pet the are using, pretty sure they would tell you that this isn't the case.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
